about me

Kim Howell

Designer and front-end developer

With over 10 years of experience in both Australia and the UK I am confident, committed and comfortable working from a brief and developing innovative design concepts for print, web, publishing and advertising. I bring to any new role experience, reliability, creativity, and the ability to deliver.

Employment

Hitachi Construction Machinery (Australia)
2011 - present

As Senior Graphic Designer at Hitachi Construction Machinery Australia, a leading manufacturer of construction and mining equipment, I am responsible for the design and development of all print, web and marketing materials. As brand custodian I ensure that all materials are produced in accordance with strict brand guidelines.

DESIGN

  • Creation of bespoke posters
  • logo design
  • Website design
  • Design of video on demand microsites

WEB DEVELOPMENT

  • Manage the functionality of intranet and internal micro sites
  • Build and development of video on demand microsites and site promotion
  • Implementation of Ominture tracking of video on demand and intranet sites
  • Front end website development

Twofour/GlaxoSmithKline
2006 – 2011

Twofour is a market-leading digital agency working with the world’s biggest brands, broadcasters and the public sector. I was employed by Twofour to provide GSK, one of the leading pharmaceutical companies in the world, with a variety of design services.
